        note: "Built the Red Army from a revolutionary militia into a 5-million-man fighting force by hiring former Tsarist officers (under threat) and imposing iron discipline. Traveled the fronts on his armored train, showing up wherever the situation was worst. Won the civil war. Lost the succession fight to Stalin. Fled to Mexico. Was assassinated with an ice axe in 1940. The twentieth century was unkind to its most interesting people.",
