    summary: "The First Libyan Civil War (2011) was an armed uprising against Muammar Gaddafi's 42-year dictatorship, part of the Arab Spring. After Gaddafi's forces besieged rebel-held Benghazi, a NATO intervention authorized by UN Security Council Resolution 1973 tipped the balance. Gaddafi was captured and killed in October 2011, but Libya subsequently collapsed into factional warfare that continues to destabilize the country.",
