    summary: "The War on ISIL (2014–2019, ongoing operations) was a multinational military campaign against the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIS/ISIL/Daesh), which seized vast territory across Iraq and Syria in 2014, declaring a 'caliphate.' A US-led coalition of 80+ nations, combined with Iraqi forces, Kurdish Peshmerga, Syrian Democratic Forces, and Russian/Iranian-backed Syrian government forces, destroyed ISIS's territorial caliphate by 2019. However, ISIS continues as an insurgency.",
