      "ISIS emerged from al-Qaeda in Iraq (AQI), which had fought US forces during the Iraq War. Under Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi, it expanded into Syria's civil war.",
      "In June 2014, ISIS captured Mosul, Iraq's second-largest city, and declared a caliphate spanning Iraq and Syria.",
      "ISIS's brutality — mass executions, beheadings, enslavement of Yazidis, destruction of cultural heritage — shocked the world.",
