    summary: "The Myanmar Civil War (2021–present) erupted after the military (Tatmadaw) staged a coup on February 1, 2021, overthrowing the elected government of Aung San Suu Kyi. Massive pro-democracy protests were met with lethal force, driving the formation of the People's Defence Forces (PDF) and an alliance with ethnic armed organizations. By 2024, the resistance had seized significant territory, and the military junta faces its most serious challenge since independence.",
    background: [
      "Myanmar's military ruled the country from 1962 to 2011; a partial democratic transition allowed Suu Kyi's NLD to win elections in 2015 and 2020.",
      "The military refused to accept the NLD's landslide 2020 victory, claiming fraud, and staged a coup on February 1, 2021.",
      "Massive nationwide protests (the Spring Revolution) were met with lethal force; security forces killed over 1,500 protesters in the first year.",
      "The National Unity Government (NUG), formed by ousted lawmakers, organized the People's Defence Forces and allied with ethnic armed organizations.",
    ],
